cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for sparse hierarchical representation learning on graph-structured data with edge features, specifically for molecules relevant to drug discovery. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and can also be related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) due to the use of graph-convolutional architectures. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for classification and regression tasks.
